.:: Puzzle 2x6-Level-3-16::.
The people use 6 different means of transport: trike, subway, quad-bike, taxi, train, snowmobile
There 6 different types of food: cabbage, corn, garlic, peach, pear, pepper
 1. the person driving the trike is on the left of the person driving the train##1
 2. the person driving the quad-bike is on the right of the person eating garlic##1
 3. the person driving the subway is between the person driving the snowmobile and the person eating peach##2
 4. the person eating pepper is on the left of the person driving the trike##1
 5. the person eating pear is on the left or right of the person driving the train##3
 6. the person driving the quad-bike is on the left of the person driving the trike##1
 7. the person eating pear is between the person driving the snowmobile and the person driving the train##2
 8. the person eating garlic is on the far left##1
 9. the person driving the quad-bike is on the left or right of the person eating cabbage##3
10. the person eating pear is between the person driving the snowmobile and the person driving the train##2

.:: Answer ::.
|            |    1     |       2       |      3      |   4   |  5   |   6   |
| Transport   | taxi | quad-bike | trike | train | subway | snowmobile |
| Food       | garlic   | pepper        | cabbage     | peach | pear | corn  |

